article.headline: Cal Poly 89, UC Irvine 80
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. (AP) -- Dawin Whiten scored a career-high 31 points and matched a school record with eight 3-pointers Saturday as Cal Poly beat UC Irvine 89-80. Whiten, who sat out Thursday's loss to Long Beach State with an ankle injury, was 9-for-13 from the floor and 8-for-11 from 3-point range. The eight 3s tied a school record last matched by Watende Favors on Dec. 6, 1997. Cal Poly hit 16 of 32 from behind the arc as a team and won despite hitting just 13 of 27 free throws. The Mustangs (12-10, 4-5 Big West) held a 50-43 lead at halftime and pushed the lead to double digits early in the second half, handing the Anteaters (11-15, 5-7) their 11th loss in 13 road games. UC Irvine was led by Mark Kelley's 18 points. Patrick Sanders added 16 points. Derek Stockalper added 15 points and 11 rebounds for the Mustangs, and Trae Clark had eight assists.
